text.section:
Each soil and water conservation district which receives or uses the equipment referred to in KRS 262.610 shall maintain its public records to show for each piece of equipment:
The hours same has worked on each job in each district;
The amounts collected from each job in each district;
The expense of repairing, moving, manning and other usual costs of operation; and
The amount paid by each district for the purpose of amortizing the commission's investment in the equipment.
